This is a duplicate workspace of CW50461, created to change supplier name.

A booking tool system, provided by BookingLive, is used by three different
business areas across TfL which enables them to do the following activities:
- Buskers to book pitches at tube stations;
- Charity collectors to book to collect donations at tube stations;
- Boats to book berths at London River Services (LRS) piers.

To carry out refurbishment and improvement works at Gloucester Road and High Barnet Underground Stations and Rickmansworth Area Office. The main scope of works will be premises focussed, including:  

 Decoration, painting, tiling, flooring, ceiling and walls; 

Replacement of finishes, fixtures and fittings; 

Sanitaryware; sinks, showers, toilets; 

Mechanical; water pipework, heating, ventilation 

The project will be focusing on the following rooms:

CW created for Expenditure type Agreements with no previous/ expired governance


This Consolidated Exempt Request covers:

A number of live signed agreements with Network Rail (NR) and Train Operating Companies (TOCs) entered into by LU during years 1987 – 2018 in accordance with the governance process valid at the time, that do not have electronic Governance paper trail. This Request brings them into compliance with the current existing governance process;

Agreements “in perpetuity” with NR;

Agreements with an end date in the period between now and March 2026, which meet the following 2 criteria:

Current live agreements with NR that must be extended/renewed, as there is no other company able to provide the contracted services;

Station Access Agreements (SAA) with TOCs that will either be extended following the DfT’s extensions of the franchise(s) or awarded to a new franchisee.

CW for Revenue generating contracts with no previous or expired governance.

