This is to provide a service to the Engineering and Asset Strategy and PMO (Programme Management Office) directorates. The requirement is the production of a Value Stream Map to support future process improvement to the resource allocation tool – SmartCore used across TfL owned by PMO. The service offering should take account of the existing process described in the attached Visio diagram (limits of scope drawn in using a green boundary) currently Engineering focussed. The longer-term aim (out of scope) is to improve the effectiveness of SmartCore as a resource management tool. TfL Engineering and Asset Strategy will provide embedded TfL resources to support. Estimated 2 x FTE (Full Time Equivalent) can supply supporting feedback on existing challenges. There will be one phase to this work;
?Production of the current state Value Stream Map of the resourcing process (see attachment) withinengineering.
?Identification of potential process improvements across all TfL. Engineering and Asse
